  <!-- 1.0 Founding Morals -->
  <div class="container section" id="founding-morals">
    <h2>1.0 - Founding Morals of the FIB</h2>
    <h3>1.1 Professionalism</h3>
    <p>Represent yourself and your department positively. Speak to peers, superiors, and subordinates in a manner that is becoming of the position you hold.</p>
    <h3>1.2 Respect</h3>
    <p>Treat others with dignity and fairness. Avoid creating a toxic environment by disrespecting, harassing, or bullying members in any way.</p>
    <h3>1.3 Integrity</h3>
    <p>Do what is right even when no one is looking. Take responsibility for your actions and always strive to make correct decisions.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- 2.0 Duties & Code of Conduct -->
  <div class="container section" id="duties">
    <h2>2.0 - Duties & Code of Conduct</h2>
    <h3>2.1 Duties</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Conduct professional investigations against gangs, violent criminals, and terrorists.</li>
      <li>Develop techniques, systems, and equipment to strengthen law enforcement.</li>
      <li>Coordinate inter-agency efforts for critical infrastructure protection.</li>
      <li>Locate and apprehend fugitives and high-value targets.</li>
      <li>Conduct investigations to dismantle criminal enterprises.</li>
      <li>Gather and assess intelligence on criminal activity.</li>
      <li>Establish outreach programs and conduct law enforcement training.</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>2.2 Code of Conduct</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Follow strict department rules; messing around on duty is not allowed.</li>
      <li>One-strike policy: violation can result in termination.</li>
      <li>Complete training within 14 days of interview.</li>
      <li>Complete minimum required hours.</li>
      <li>Treat everyone with respect regardless of rank, age, gender, or religion.</li>
      <li>Declare gang affiliation to high command if applicable.</li>
      <li>Leaking documents will lead to blacklisting and disciplinary action.</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>2.3 Conduct on Duty</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Follow Global SOP and department procedures.</li>
      <li>Have correct headtag, radio, uniform, car, and be in assigned RTOs.</li>
      <li>Weapon Loadouts: Combat Pistols, Carbine Rifles*, Pump Shotguns, Taser, Beanbag Shotgun, Nightstick.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- 3.0 Chain of Command -->
  <div class="container section" id="chain-of-command">
    <h2>3.0 - Chain of Command</h2>
    <h3>3.1 Rank Structure</h3>
    <p>High Command: Director, Deputy Director, Assistant Director, Executive Director, Chief of Staff</p>
    <p>Trial High Command: Commander</p>
    <p>Low Command: Captain, Lieutenant, Senior Section Chief, Section Chief</p>
    <p>Trial Low Command: Section Officer, Senior Special Agent in Charge</p>
    <p>Supervisors: Special Agent in Charge, Assistant Special Agent in Charge, Supervisory Special Agent</p>
    <p>Agents: Senior Special Agent, Special Agent, Senior Agent, Agent</p>
    <p>Trainee Agents: Probationary Agent</p>
  </div>

  <!-- 4.0 Subdivisions -->
  <div class="container section" id="subdivisions">
    <h2>4.0 - Subdivisions</h2>
    <h3>4.1 Hostage Rescue Team</h3>
    <p>HRT handles immediate tactical intervention with precision and minimal collateral damage, using advanced training and coordination.</p>
    <h3>4.2 Field Training Division</h3>
    <p>FTD trains future agents and ensures they meet promotional requirements through ride-alongs and mentorship.</p>
    <h3>4.3 Violent Gang Task Force</h3>
    <p>VGTF performs undercover operations, SEMI-TAC support, and warrants on gangs across San Andreas.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- 5.0 Promotions & Demotions -->
  <div class="container section" id="promotions">
    <h2>5.0 - Promotions & Demotions</h2>
    <h3>5.1 General Promotions</h3>
    <p>Rank-specific requirements must be met. Promotions are decided weekly. Evaluation requests can be submitted within 24 hours.</p>
    <h3>5.2 Field Promotions</h3>
    <p>Field promotions occur occasionally. Punishment history is considered, and cooldowns apply post-promotion.</p>
    <h3>5.3 Disciplinary Action</h3>
    <p>Disciplinary actions include strikes, demotions, and inactivity warnings. The FIB uses a two-strike policy.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- 6.0 Department Policies -->
  <div class="container section" id="policies">
    <h2>6.0 - Department Policies</h2>
    <h3>6.1 Leave of Absence (LOA)</h3>
    <p>Requests must be approved by high or low command. LOAs cannot exceed 30 days without approval. Extensions require notification; violations may result in demotion or termination.</p>
    <h3>6.2 One Strike Policy</h3>
    <p>Strict one-strike policy applies to all agents, resulting in termination or demotion for violations.</p>
    <h3>6.3 Bulletproof Vehicles</h3>
    <p>Only supervisors or authorized personnel may use bulletproof vehicles, with permission required from high command in special cases.</p>
